umeratum-circe_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:265:| `com.softwaremill.sttp.client4:circe_3` | [4.0.23<br>- 4.0.25](metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.client4/circe_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> sttp client4 circe is the Circe JSON integration module for the Scala sttp HTTP client. It adds request body serialization and response body deserialization helpers such as asJson that use Circe Encoder and Decoder instances.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.softwaremill.sttp.client4/circe_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:274:| `com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir:tapir-json-circe_3` | [1.11.25<br>- 1.13.19](metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-json-circe_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Tapir JSON Circe integrates sttp Tapir endpoints with Circe by providing JSON body and query codecs backed by Circe encoders and decoders. It lets Scala applications describe, decode, and encode JSON endpoint inputs and outputs while keeping Tapir schema information in scope.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-json-circe_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:383:| `io.circe:circe-core_3` | [0.14.10<br>- 0.15.0-M1](metadata/io.circe/circe-core_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Core provides the core JSON data model and type classes for encoding and decoding JSON in Scala. It includes the JSON AST, cursor APIs, codec abstractions, printers, parser interfaces, and standard instances used by other Circe modules.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-core_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:384:| `io.circe:circe-jawn_3` | [0.14.12<br>- 0.14.15](metadata/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Jawn integrates the Circe JSON data model with the Jawn JSON parser for Scala. It provides parser and facade implementations that read JSON text into Circe Json values and support Circe's higher-level parsing modules.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:385:| `io.circe:circe-numbers_3` | [0.14.10<br>- 0.15.0-M1](metadata/io.circe/circe-numbers_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Numbers provides numeric value support for Circe's JSON model, centered on the BiggerDecimal representation used for JSON numbers. It supplies Scala 3 JVM classes for preserving numeric precision and converting between decimal and integral forms in Circe.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-numbers_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:386:| `io.circe:circe-parser_3` | [0.14.12<br>- 0.14.15](metadata/io.circe/circe-parser_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Circe Parser provides JSON parsing functions for the Circe Scala JSON library. It exposes parser APIs that turn JSON text into Circe Json values using the Jawn-based parsing implementation.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.circe/circe-parser_3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:1047:| `org.http4s:http4s-circe_3` | [0.23.34](metadata/org.http4s/http4s-circe_3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> http4s-circe integrates the http4s HTTP toolkit with Circe JSON by providing entity encoders and decoders for JSON values and codecs. It lets Scala applications read and write JSON request and response bodies using Circe in http4s clients and servers.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.http4s/http4s-circe_3/) |\n./stats/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/0.14.12/execution-metrics.json:4:    \"library\": \"io.circe:circe-jawn_3:0.14.12\",\n./stats/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/0.14.12/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/0.14.12/src/test/scala/io_circe/circe_jawn_3/Circe_jawn_3Test.scala\",\n./stats/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/0.14.12/execution-metrics.json:53:      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/io.circe/circe-jawn_3/0.14.12/reachability-metadata.json\"\n./stats/io.circe/circe-parser_3/0.14.12/execution-metrics.json:4:    \"library\": \"io.circe:circe-parser_3:0.14.12\",\n./stats/io.circe/circe-parser_3/0.14.12/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\":